---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import Email from '../components/Email.astro';
import { SITE } from '../lib/site';

const title = 'Privacy policy';
const description =
  'How Apriori Studio collects, uses and protects information you share with us through this website.';
const updated = '2026-05-04';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 py-10 md:py-14">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[
      { href: '/', label: 'Home' },
      { href: '/privacy', label: 'Privacy policy' },
    ]} />

    <header class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Privacy policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-ink-soft)]">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose-body">
      <p>
        This page explains what information Apriori Studio (operating as Apriori Ltd, a company
        registered in England and Wales) collects through aprioristudio.com, what we do with it,
        and how you can ask us to delete it. We try to write this in plain English. If anything
        is unclear, email us at <Email address={SITE.email.contact} />
        and we'll explain.
      </p>

      <h2>Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        Apriori Ltd ("we," "us," "our") is the data controller for personal data submitted
        through this website. Our registered office is in Cambridge, United Kingdom. You can reach
        us at <Email address={SITE.email.contact} />.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <p>
        We collect personal data only when you actively give it to us — typically by filling in
        the contact form on this site. That data consists of:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your name</li>
        <li>Your email address</li>
        <li>The subject and content of your message</li>
        <li>Your IP address and the browser/device information your browser sends with the request (used for spam protection and abuse prevention)</li>
        <li>The page you came from (HTTP referer), if your browser sent it</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not use cookies on this website. We do not run third-party analytics that track
        you across other sites. We do not sell or share your information with advertisers.
      </p>

      <h2>Why we collect it</h2>
      <p>
        We use the information you submit through the contact form to reply to your enquiry,
        to discuss potential project work, and to keep a record of correspondence. The legal
        basis under UK GDPR is "legitimate interests" (replying to a person who has contacted
        us asking for a reply) and "performance of a contract / steps prior to entering a
        contract."
      </p>

      <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
      <p>
        Contact form submissions are kept for up to twenty-four months from the last
        correspondence, after which they're deleted from our systems. If our exchange leads to
        a project, we keep relevant communications for the duration of the project plus six
        years (UK statutory record-keeping for limited companies).
      </p>

      <h2>Who we share it with</h2>
      <p>
        We don't share personal data with third parties for marketing or commercial purposes.
        The information you submit is processed by:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Our hosting provider (the server that runs this website)</li>
        <li>Our email provider (the mail server that delivers messages between us)</li>
        <li>Where strictly necessary, professional advisers (accountants, lawyers) under confidentiality</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not transfer your data outside the United Kingdom or European Economic Area for
        marketing purposes. Some of our infrastructure providers may store backups in the EU;
        these transfers are covered by the appropriate safeguards (Standard Contractual
        Clauses or adequacy decisions).
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Under UK GDPR you have the right to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Ask for a copy of any personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li>Ask us to correct inaccurate data</li>
        <li>Ask us to delete data we no longer need</li>
        <li>Object to processing in certain circumstances</li>
        <li>Lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at ico.org.uk</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, email us at
        <Email address={SITE.email.contact} />. We'll respond within
        thirty days.
      </p>

      <h2>Security</h2>
      <p>
        We use HTTPS across the whole site. Submissions to our contact form are stored in a
        database that's accessible only over a private network connection from the web server.
        We apply security updates promptly and back up the database regularly. No system is
        perfectly secure, but we treat personal data with the level of care we'd want for our
        own.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        If we change this policy materially, we'll update the date at the top of this page.
        For minor wording changes (clarifications, typo fixes), we'll just publish the
        updated text.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
